<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06048088 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06048088 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  Our spies in Tokyo report that American and British movie stars continue toflock to Japan to make commercials, much to the joy of that country's fans andtheir own gaping wallets.;    Charlie Sheen, for instance, sells shoes inJapan, which we believe we have mentioned before. But have we reported that healso appears on the tube for Tokyo Gas Co., calmly smiling next to sign withthe fascinating slogan, &quot;My life, my gas.&quot;?  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  JAPANESE COMMERCIALS WITH WESTERN FACES  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  People .Information in this column is from Mercury news wire services.  </MEMO><TEXT>     Now add Britain's Daniel Day-Lewis to the list. His marketability isensured by the Academy Award he won last year for best actor.;    The star of&quot;My Left Foot&quot; sells a men's cosmetics line, uttering two words: &quot;It's pure.&quot;  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Jim Jeffress  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  SAN JOSE MERCURY NEWS  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910217  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Sunday  </DAY><MONTH>  February  </MONTH><PG.COL>  2A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  126  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Sunday February 17, 199100048088,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>